The only other thing I can think of is using some sort of proxy for the model:

```python
class ProxyModel:
    def __init__(self, model=None):
        self._model = model

        if self._model:
            self.DoesNotExist = model.DoesNotExist
        else:
            self.DoesNotExist = ObjectDoesNotExist

	def __getattr__(self, name):
        return getattr(self._model, name)
```

And then in the `QuerySetSequence` we would do `self.model = ProxyModel(model)`.

This can get finicky, but at least gives a bit more control and doesn't monkey-patch anything.

